# Force LF line endings for files where byte-equivalence matters
# across platforms (Windows checkouts would otherwise autoconvert to
# CRLF and break Rust-side byte comparisons).
#
# `toolr-manifest.json` is serialised by
# `toolr_core::build_fragment::serialise_fragment` with literal `\n`
# line terminators, and `toolr self build-manifest --check` compares
# the on-disk file byte-for-byte against the regenerated output.
*.json text eol=lf

# `skills/*/references/*.md` are generated by
# `cargo xtask build-skill-refs` and byte-compared by `--check`.
# Same byte-equivalence story as the JSON snapshots above — Windows
# checkouts with `core.autocrlf=true` would otherwise rewrite the
# committed files to CRLF and fail the check.
skills/*/references/*.md text eol=lf
